The first column (index 0) is the cost, and the next m columns (indices 1 to m) are the skills. So in C, the array c is [n][m+1], where c[i][0] is the cost, c[i][1] to c[i][m] are the skills. So for each course i in the subset (mask has bit i set), we loop over each of the m skills (indices 1 to m):

for (skill = 1; skill <= m; skill++) {

