Then check if all totals >=x. If yes, then compare sum_cost with min_cost. This way, the cost is computed once, and the totals are computed per skill. This approach reduces the inner loops. Wait, this is better. Because for each course in the subset, we can loop over the m skills and add to the totals. This way, the code for each course in the subset is:

