This is better. Now, the variables: We need to read n, m, x. The courses are stored in a 2D array. Let's say:

int c[21][21]; // assuming n up to 20, m up to 20.

Now, handling input:

In C, reading the first line: n, m, x. 

We can read using scanf:

scanf("%d % d %d", &n, &m, &x);

Then for each of the n courses:

for (int i=0; i <n; i++) {

    for (int j=0; j <=m; j++) {

